<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="acknowledge-vt">acknowledge <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əkˈnɒlɪdʒ/    美 /əkˈnɑːlɪdʒ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>承认</strong></h4>
<p>to accept or admit that sth is true or exists：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>acknowledge one’s error 
承认错误</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is <strong>acknowledged as / to be</strong> one of the greatest pianists. 
他被认为是最杰出的钢琴家之一。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They acknowledged (to us) that they were defeated.
他们(向我们)承认被打败了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>向...打招呼；对...作出反应</strong></h4>
<p>to show that you have seen or noticed sb / sth or received sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was standing right next to her, but she didn’t even acknowledge me. 
我就站在她旁边，可她连个招呼都不跟我打。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He acknowledged the greeting with a nod. 
他点头回应了问候。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>(公开) 感谢</strong></h4>
<p>to publicly express thanks for help you have been given：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I should like to acknowledge all the help I have received from my family.
我要感谢我的家人给予我的所有帮助。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>acknowledgement /ək'nɒlɪdʒmənt/ n   </p></div>